                <h1>Understanding Level 3 Background Check Disqualifying Offenses</h1>
                <p>Level 3 background checks often reveal serious offenses that can disqualify candidates from employment or specific roles, especially those involving vulnerable populations. Disqualifying offenses may include violent crimes, felony drug charges, sexual offenses, and other serious infractions. Understanding these disqualifiers is crucial for job seekers.</p>
